<br>
I hate the RIAA so much that I would not be unhappy if some good samaritan would go commit random acts of violence against  their offices and property though.<br>
<br>
I won't do it myself though, because I am spineless and don't wan't want to spend a lot of time in jail or owe large fines, Plus, vandalism, even against an organazation as dispicable as the RIAA, is wrong.<br>
<br>
I can boycott them though, and suggest others do the same.  I would settle for choking off those bastards cash flow till they are starving in the street begging for bread crumbs from people with honest employment.<br>
<br>
Do you think it would be ok if I posted a link here to an anti-RIAA, pro boycott site?<br>
<br>
Anyone who's ever shared a music file on their PC might benifit, but it seems kind of iffy as to if I would be breaking any rules by posting it.  <br>
<br>
Anyone with an opinion please let me know. I don't want to violate any board rules.<br>
<br>
