<br>
You spend many hours thinking up a good story.<br>
Gallons of creative fluid is spent developing it.<br>
Much stress and anxiety over whether it will sell.<br>
<br>
It sells and maybe you'll be able to afford a new car from the 3%  royalties (or atleast afford the one you have and still eat three squares a day.)<br>
<br>
someone buys a copy and posts it as a free download on their site.Everybody loves it!<br>
<br>
you sell 300 copies. You would have made the NY Times best seller list except free downloads aren't a sale.<br>
<br>
What do you have for your hard work? The warm and fuzzies of knowing people love your writing enough to want to read it, but not enough to compensate you for the pleasure of it.<br>
<br>
When are you going to do it again?<br>
<br>
Most of the people who have no problem with ripping music/movies/books tend to have a parasite mentality.<br>
